00:38:36,920 --> 00:38:38,080
The cops over there

539
00:38:38,160 --> 00:38:39,920
they're in cahoots 
with the big syndicate.

540
00:38:40,280 --> 00:38:41,720
Hey, be careful with that.

541
00:38:41,800 --> 00:38:43,600
- It's not my money. 
- I'm sorry, boss.

542
00:38:43,680 --> 00:38:45,480
- I didn't mean it. 
- Fucking moron.

543
00:38:46,040 --> 00:38:48,520
And he would not want a guy 
like you sniffing around, bro.

544
00:38:56,760 --> 00:38:57,920
How's it going?

545
00:38:58,440 --> 00:39:01,120
Holy shit, this is a big shipment.

546
00:39:03,320 --> 00:39:04,520
What's in the blinkin' thing?

547
00:39:05,080 --> 00:39:08,000
The shit that's gonna land Lendina 
on INTERPOL's Top Ten.

548
00:39:10,560 --> 00:39:11,760
This is great.

549
00:39:12,720 --> 00:39:14,960
You want more guys here, just in case 
there's any more trouble?

550
00:39:17,160 --> 00:39:21,120
Hey, don't cause any trouble 
and there won't be any trouble.

551
00:39:21,600 --> 00:39:23,320
Remember who's boss here.

552
00:39:25,000 --> 00:39:26,120
Got it.

553
00:39:28,840 --> 00:39:30,280
I gotta get my son.

554
00:39:32,080 --> 00:39:33,800
Watch this shit and be cool.

555
00:39:42,240 --> 00:39:43,520
Want me to take that?

556
00:39:44,120 --> 00:39:45,240
Thanks.

557
00:39:46,280 --> 00:39:48,600
Do you think Dad is eventually going 
to grace us with his presence?

558
00:39:48,680 --> 00:39:49,680
Or...

559
00:39:49,760 --> 00:39:50,960
Wild animals!

560
00:39:53,520 --> 00:39:55,680
Don't go too near. 
That's a wild wolf dog.

561
00:39:56,000 --> 00:39:57,480
Gotta stay locked up, that one.

562
00:39:58,560 --> 00:40:00,920
Well, Mom, you saved animals 
back when you met Dad, right?

563
00:40:02,120 --> 00:40:04,040
Among other things, but...

564
00:40:04,640 --> 00:40:06,200
You know, if you gain their trust

565
00:40:06,640 --> 00:40:08,840
and you show them that 
the world is a safe place for them--

566
00:40:08,920 --> 00:40:10,760
- World that is safe? 
- Yeah.

567
00:40:11,240 --> 00:40:12,760
What world is that?

568
00:40:14,480 --> 00:40:16,320
Okay, let's go find Dad for dinner.

569
00:40:20,160 --> 00:40:22,160
You caught a tourist, I heard.

570
00:40:22,240 --> 00:40:23,720
Did they put up much of a fight?

571
00:40:26,680 --> 00:40:28,800
What's th-- I can't hear you.

572
00:40:30,120 --> 00:40:31,560
Hey, turn that off!

573
00:40:32,320 --> 00:40:33,480
Shut it off!

574
00:40:33,560 --> 00:40:34,960
What are you, new?!

575
00:40:35,760 --> 00:40:37,320
What... what was that?

576
00:40:38,120 --> 00:40:39,840
He broke my teeth, man.

577
00:40:41,160 --> 00:40:42,440
What about your teeth?

578
00:40:43,040 --> 00:40:46,640
He crushed 'em, okay? 
He... he jus... he beat everybody.

579
00:40:47,040 --> 00:40:49,120
What the fuck are you talking about?

580
00:40:50,360 --> 00:40:51,680
Talking about the guy, okay?

581
00:40:51,760 --> 00:40:53,600
I don't think he's just a tourist!

582
00:41:00,960 --> 00:41:03,360
- Yes? 
- I've got a problem.

583
00:41:03,760 --> 00:41:05,600
Of your own making, I sense.

584
00:41:05,680 --> 00:41:08,400
Plummerville. You heard of it?

585
00:41:08,720 --> 00:41:09,880
It's a back road.

586
00:41:10,160 --> 00:41:14,360
Drugs, guns, viruses and worse 
come down from Canada

587
00:41:14,440 --> 00:41:15,960
and go on to points unknown.

588
00:41:16,560 --> 00:41:19,200
Alright. Well, where does 
the buck stop here?

589
00:41:19,560 --> 00:41:20,880
There are layers.

590
00:41:22,080 --> 00:41:26,600
Possibly an individual, 
a unique individual, called Lendina.

591
00:41:28,320 --> 00:41:29,480
Lendina.

592
00:41:39,120 --> 00:41:40,800
- Guy in the white? 
- Yes, ma'am.

593
00:41:44,760 --> 00:41:47,320
- No, no. No new dealer. 
- This requires a woman's touch.

594
00:41:47,640 --> 00:41:49,600
I'm winning. On a roll here.

595
00:41:49,680 --> 00:41:50,920
Congratulations.

596
00:41:51,000 --> 00:41:52,600
Let's see how your luck goes.

597
00:41:55,840 --> 00:41:57,520
Beautiful. I split.

598
00:41:58,760 --> 00:41:59,800
Sure.

599
00:42:00,640 --> 00:42:02,600
- Hit me. 
- How's your trip been going so far?

600
00:42:02,680 --> 00:42:03,760
Shut up and deal.

601
00:42:04,520 --> 00:42:07,760
Plummerville is critical 
to Lendina's larger empire.

602
00:42:07,840 --> 00:42:09,040
Oh, shit.

603
00:42:11,440 --> 00:42:12,760
It happens.

604
00:42:14,080 --> 00:42:15,480
A lone wolf.

605
00:42:15,920 --> 00:42:20,360
Operates unburdened 
by any constraints at all.

606
00:42:21,200 --> 00:42:24,320
You piss off the Russians, 
they come to your house with guns.

607
00:42:24,400 --> 00:42:27,320
Lendina and her squad will slay 
your family on the front lawn

608
00:42:27,400 --> 00:42:29,360
and force you to watch

609
00:42:29,440 --> 00:42:33,000
if you disrupt 
their situations any further.

610
00:42:36,800 --> 00:42:38,120
Yes!

611
00:42:39,560 --> 00:42:40,960
Pay me!

612
00:42:46,360 --> 00:42:47,800
You're a winner.

613
00:42:48,600 --> 00:42:50,240
Ma'am, I swear I knew nothing.

614
00:42:53,880 --> 00:42:55,080
What's happening?!

615
00:42:58,440 --> 00:43:00,880
Nobody cheats in my casino!

616
00:43:07,600 --> 00:43:09,920
You'll want to 
de-escalate the situation.

617
00:43:10,960 --> 00:43:14,360
I mean, do you got 
any intel, an address

618
00:43:14,440 --> 00:43:15,440
or anything?

619
00:43:16,320 --> 00:43:19,360
I'll give you a lead. 
But hear me on this.

620
00:43:21,240 --> 00:43:22,480
You're on your own, Hutch.

621
00:43:23,120 --> 00:43:26,760
Killer, I'm so sorry 
that you had to see that.

622
00:43:27,320 --> 00:43:31,040
My little baby should never see 
those terrible, terrible people.

623
00:43:32,640 --> 00:43:34,040
What about them back there?

624
00:43:34,640 --> 00:43:36,880
Leave no witnesses. Burn it down.

625
00:43:36,960 --> 00:43:37,960
You got it.

626
00:43:38,200 --> 00:43:39,480
Let's go for a walk.

627
00:43:46,840 --> 00:43:48,520
That was fast. Did it hurt?

628
00:43:49,280 --> 00:43:50,680
No, I'm fine.

629
00:43:51,080 --> 00:43:52,480
Maybe this is too soon.

630
00:43:52,920 --> 00:43:54,440
Dad, really, I'm fine.

631
00:43:54,840 --> 00:43:56,320
My arm's feeling good.

632
00:43:57,480 --> 00:43:58,560
Hold on.

633
00:44:02,280 --> 00:44:03,920
Max, I have to take this damn call.

634
00:44:04,000 --> 00:44:05,000
Won't be long.

635
00:44:05,960 --> 00:44:06,960
What?

636
00:44:07,040 --> 00:44:10,840
Well, that's no way 
to treat your business partner.

637
00:44:11,280 --> 00:44:12,680
Ex-partner.

638
00:44:12,840 --> 00:44:14,440
This is my last shipment.

639
00:44:15,240 --> 00:44:18,120
- Goodness. 
- My father's debt is all paid up.

640
00:44:19,000 --> 00:44:20,200
I can count.

641
00:44:21,440 --> 00:44:26,840
This, you know, pays off 
the last of our debt.

642
00:44:28,080 --> 00:44:31,480
By my calculations, 
the debt will never be paid off.

643
00:44:31,560 --> 00:44:32,880
No.

644
00:44:32,960 --> 00:44:34,200
That's bullshit and you know it.

645
00:44:36,680 --> 00:44:38,440
Ain't nothing funny 
about what I said.

646
00:44:39,720 --> 00:44:40,720
Your father died

647
00:44:40,800 --> 00:44:42,640
because he was distracted.

648
00:44:43,160 --> 00:44:44,840
Are you distracted?

649
00:44:44,920 --> 00:44:46,320
I'm not my dad.

650
00:44:46,520 --> 00:44:47,840
It's over.

651
00:44:49,440 --> 00:44:52,720
Well then, we'll see.

652
00:44:54,000 --> 00:44:55,080
Well...

653
00:44:57,320 --> 00:44:58,480
Hello?

654
00:45:05,240 --> 00:45:07,160
Hey, Max! Where are you going?

655
00:45:17,040 --> 00:45:18,040
Sheriff.

656
00:45:18,120 --> 00:45:19,640
You can just call me Abel.

657
00:45:20,760 --> 00:45:22,000
Sheriff.

658
00:45:22,080 --> 00:45:25,200
I need to make sure Wyatt 
hasn't forgotten who he works for.

659
00:45:26,360 --> 00:45:29,360
Take something that really 
matters to him.

660
00:45:29,840 --> 00:45:30,840
Got it.

661
00:45:38,360 --> 00:45:39,680
Mom, it's your turn.

662
00:45:41,080 --> 00:45:42,720
- Hey, Mom. 
- Yes?

663
00:45:42,800 --> 00:45:44,200
Is Dad in trouble again?

664
00:45:45,400 --> 00:45:46,800
Why? Do you know something?

665
00:45:47,800 --> 00:45:49,560
No, that's why... no.

666
00:45:49,640 --> 00:45:50,800
I'm sure he'll be--

667
00:45:54,080 --> 00:45:55,320
No, honey. Let me.

668
00:46:05,640 --> 00:46:08,600
Hamburgers and s'mores

669
00:46:08,680 --> 00:46:10,400
for dinner tonight!

670
00:46:10,480 --> 00:46:12,120
- So nutritious. 
- Yay!

671
00:46:13,360 --> 00:46:15,360
Your dad's running late.

672
00:46:15,440 --> 00:46:17,240
But come with me.

673
00:46:17,320 --> 00:46:19,440
I promise you it's the way to go.

674
00:46:19,960 --> 00:46:20,960
Sammy, come on. Help me pack up.

675
00:46:21,040 --> 00:46:23,200
- You... you talked to Hutch? 
- Talk later.

676
00:46:23,280 --> 00:46:25,480
- Gotta move. 
- Okay.

677
00:46:29,400 --> 00:46:32,840
Walk in real smooth.

678
00:46:34,160 --> 00:46:36,080
Keep everything room temp.

679
00:46:36,160 --> 00:46:37,440
Yeah.

680
00:46:37,520 --> 00:46:38,880
No escalating.

681
00:46:39,440 --> 00:46:41,040
De-escalate.

682
00:46:41,720 --> 00:46:43,560
Lead by example.

683
00:46:44,960 --> 00:46:47,680
Hey, fellas. What a mix-up.

684
00:46:51,400 --> 00:46:53,320
It's a big shipment, 
but I guarantee you

685
00:46:53,400 --> 00:46:54,880
we can do more next time.

686
00:46:55,200 --> 00:46:56,880
Except those paintings are a bitch.

687
00:46:57,360 --> 00:46:58,960
But you gotta see what's in here.

688
00:47:02,800 --> 00:47:06,360
Here is the special thing 
the boss lady asked for.

689
00:47:07,120 --> 00:47:09,040
Wyatt's spoiled son.

690
00:47:10,680 --> 00:47:12,400
Now, I want you to tell the boss

691
00:47:12,480 --> 00:47:16,680
that I said it was a pleasure 
to be of service. Okay?

692
00:47:17,640 --> 00:47:18,880
You understand?

693
00:47:19,920 --> 00:47:21,840
Or do I need to get 
a fucking translator?

694
00:47:24,600 --> 00:47:26,200
I need to get a fucking translator.

695
00:47:28,640 --> 00:47:29,680
Hey, fellas.

696
00:47:30,200 --> 00:47:31,840
What the fuck! 
How did you get in here?

697
00:47:32,680 --> 00:47:33,840
The door.

698
00:47:34,800 --> 00:47:35,800
Is that gasoline?

699
00:47:36,600 --> 00:47:37,760
You're quick.

700
00:47:42,040 --> 00:47:43,440
Now, listen, I could torch this money

701
00:47:43,520 --> 00:47:44,640
and it'd go up in a flash

702
00:47:44,720 --> 00:47:47,040
and whatever's in those barrels 
would go boom

703
00:47:47,120 --> 00:47:48,960
and most of you wouldn't 
make it out of here.

704
00:47:49,400 --> 00:47:52,280
And those who do 
will have to answer to Lendina.

705
00:47:53,440 --> 00:47:55,760
I'm guessing this is all hers.

706
00:47:57,320 --> 00:47:59,040
So then, what the fuck do you want?

707
00:48:01,520 --> 00:48:02,760
Okay, well...

708
00:48:03,600 --> 00:48:04,960
I want a break.

709
00:48:05,040 --> 00:48:06,080
A break?

710
00:48:06,600 --> 00:48:08,920
I just want a fucking break.

711
00:48:09,400 --> 00:48:13,800
So, if I walk out of here, 
you leave me and my family alone.

712
00:48:14,240 --> 00:48:15,800
Because that's all I want.

713
00:48:15,880 --> 00:48:17,920
To de-escalate this.

714
00:48:19,360 --> 00:48:21,120
Are you fucking kidding me?

715
00:48:21,920 --> 00:48:23,000
From the moment you've shown up

716
00:48:23,080 --> 00:48:25,240
you've put my men in the fucking ER.

717
00:48:25,320 --> 00:48:27,600
There's no way 
you were just some family man.

718
00:48:29,200 --> 00:48:31,320
De-escalate? Fuck you!

719
00:48:31,720 --> 00:48:34,160
Plummerville was A-OK 
before you showed up.

720
00:48:35,480 --> 00:48:36,920
Wherever I go...

721
00:48:38,720 --> 00:48:41,320
I could so easily kill you right now.

722
00:48:42,960 --> 00:48:43,960
But...

723
00:48:48,280 --> 00:48:49,520
You're lucky.

724
00:48:51,080 --> 00:48:52,840
You catch me on a good day.

725
00:48:56,240 --> 00:48:57,400
Go.

726
00:48:57,720 --> 00:48:59,360
Get the fuck out of here.

727
00:49:02,000 --> 00:49:03,720
Go before I change my mind.

728
00:49:11,760 --> 00:49:14,520
Will you fucking pick him up?! 
Jesus Christ!

729
00:49:15,560 --> 00:49:16,880
Help, please!

730
00:49:17,680 --> 00:49:18,680
Help me!

731
00:49:56,320 --> 00:49:58,200
You're on my last fucking nerve!

732
00:49:58,280 --> 00:50:00,640
I told you to get the fuck out--

733
00:50:01,480 --> 00:50:03,080
Who the fuck is this guy?!

734
00:50:03,920 --> 00:50:05,560
No... no!

735
00:50:08,040 --> 00:50:09,520
No... no!

736
00:50:09,600 --> 00:50:11,280
Please, wait! Wait!

737
00:51:26,200 --> 00:51:27,560
Okay, let's go.

738
00:51:36,480 --> 00:51:37,600
Stop, motherfucker!

739
00:52:01,600 --> 00:52:02,680
Fuck!

740
00:52:02,880 --> 00:52:03,880
Fuck!

741
00:52:15,720 --> 00:52:17,520
Fuck! Fuck!

742
00:52:35,400 --> 00:52:36,640
How much do we lose?

743
00:52:36,720 --> 00:52:39,000
Everything. The cash, the chemicals.

744
00:52:39,080 --> 00:52:40,080
The bio-case.

745
00:52:40,520 --> 00:52:42,240
- No. 
- All of it.

746
00:52:42,520 --> 00:52:45,400
Wiped out all our men 
and got away with Wyatt's son.

747
00:52:50,760 --> 00:52:52,160
Who is this zealot?

748
00:52:52,480 --> 00:52:54,000
Nothing about him is turning up.

749
00:52:54,080 --> 00:52:56,200
There is one oddity.

750
00:52:57,320 --> 00:52:59,360
He had a family with him.

751
00:52:59,680 --> 00:53:04,960
My valuable shipment 
was blown up by a man

752
00:53:05,040 --> 00:53:08,960
who's a tourist 
on a fucking family vacation?

753
00:53:11,160 --> 00:53:13,680
Does nobody 
play by the rules anymore?!

754
00:53:14,240 --> 00:53:15,880
Jesus fucking Christ!

755
00:53:16,920 --> 00:53:18,240
I don't know who the fuck you are

756
00:53:18,320 --> 00:53:20,520
but you crossed the line, asshole.

757
00:53:21,360 --> 00:53:22,600
Sheriff.

758
00:53:24,920 --> 00:53:26,600
What do you know about this threat?

759
00:53:26,680 --> 00:53:28,720
I don't know, okay?

760
00:53:28,800 --> 00:53:30,160
But I sent you the pictures.

761
00:53:30,240 --> 00:53:32,120
And they haven't checked 
out of the hotel.

762
00:53:32,520 --> 00:53:33,840
You might want to bring 
some others, alright?

763
00:53:33,920 --> 00:53:35,400
How... how many of your

764
00:53:35,480 --> 00:53:38,360
I guess, soldiers can you bring 
with you? Because he's--

765
00:53:38,440 --> 00:53:41,240
Shut the fuck up. I'm on my way.

766
00:53:42,120 --> 00:53:43,800
This guy's an idiot.

767
00:53:46,800 --> 00:53:48,480
- Hey, son. 
- Look who finally shows up.

768
00:53:48,560 --> 00:53:50,840
Hey, Dad. Everybody good?

769
00:53:50,920 --> 00:53:53,120
Everybody's doing great.

770
00:53:53,200 --> 00:53:55,920
Your son swings an axe like a pro.

771
00:53:56,680 --> 00:53:57,800
Dad.

772
00:53:58,080 --> 00:53:59,800
- Sammy. 
- Where were you?

773
00:54:01,120 --> 00:54:02,280
Hey, Brady, that's Max.

774
00:54:02,360 --> 00:54:04,560
I brought him here, so be cool.

775
00:54:09,920 --> 00:54:10,960
We good?

776
00:54:11,360 --> 00:54:12,440
Yeah.

777
00:54:13,000 --> 00:54:14,240
Let's go outside.

778
00:54:14,520 --> 00:54:17,640
How'd you get that shiner, 
country boy? Kidding.

779
00:54:17,720 --> 00:54:19,240
Are you stayin' for the night?

780
00:54:19,320 --> 00:54:20,880
I would... I would love to stay

781
00:54:20,960 --> 00:54:23,920
but I still got 
some heavy lifting to do.

782
00:54:24,000 --> 00:54:26,800
Oh, yeah. You're right about that.

783
00:54:31,840 --> 00:54:33,760
Let's go, Sammy.

784
00:54:34,240 --> 00:54:35,480
Come on.

785
00:54:36,280 --> 00:54:38,160
You can light the fire.

786
00:54:48,520 --> 00:54:49,920
Arm's length, Hutch.

787
00:54:50,480 --> 00:54:52,800
You were supposed 
to keep danger at arm's length!

788
00:54:53,640 --> 00:54:55,160
I didn't mean to...

789
00:54:56,760 --> 00:54:58,720
Hutch, you promised me.

790
00:54:59,920 --> 00:55:01,320
You promised.

791
00:55:02,480 --> 00:55:04,280
You broke your promise.

792
00:55:06,640 --> 00:55:08,080
I don't have...

793
00:55:09,720 --> 00:55:11,600
I don't have control over this.

794
00:55:11,880 --> 00:55:16,080
I'm just realizing that 
you should get away...

795
00:55:19,160 --> 00:55:20,480
from me.

796
00:55:24,120 --> 00:55:25,480
Becca.

797
00:55:27,080 --> 00:55:29,680
Becca, I'm not asking.

798
00:55:32,920 --> 00:55:34,640
You don't tell me what to do.

799
00:55:36,240 --> 00:55:38,200
You were a lot of things.

800
00:55:39,120 --> 00:55:41,320
But most of all, you're a dad.

801
00:55:42,320 --> 00:55:43,800
And you're my guy.

802
00:55:45,480 --> 00:55:46,760
So, go fix that shit.

803
00:55:54,080 --> 00:55:56,480
Come on, Sean. 
Answer your damn phone.

804
00:55:57,520 --> 00:55:59,440
Come on. Come on. Come on.

805
00:56:13,120 --> 00:56:14,120
You.

806
00:56:14,480 --> 00:56:16,400
What the hell are you 
still doing to my town?

807
00:56:16,480 --> 00:56:18,160
Well, I could use your help.

